<h1 align="center"><strong>Competition rules</strong><strong> </strong></h1>
<p align="center">&nbsp;</p>
<p>All band members must be 18 years old or over, any one younger wishing  to enter a band competition should register their details stating &ldquo;Junior&rdquo; at  the top of the form, dependant upon the number of junior applicants a junior  competition may follow.</p>
<p>THERE ARE NO RESTRICTIONS ON MUSIC CATEGORY, STYLE, GENRE; MATERIAL MAY  BE ORIGINAL OR THAT OF OTHERS.</p>
<p>Bands will perform a 30 minute set.<br>
  The senior competition will be held over 5 weekends.<br>
  Round 1 will consist of approx 4 bands playing per night, 2 of which  will go through to round 2.<br>
  Round 1 will be held over 5 nights (5 consecutive Friday and Saturdays)</p>
<p>Round 2 will consist of approx 10 bands playing over 3 nights,(again  consecutive Friday and Saturday nights following on immediately from round 1 ),  approx 3 bands per night one band from each night will be selected to perform  in the grand finale.</p>
<p>Approx 3 bands will perform in the final with one being declared all out  winner and receiving</p>
<h1 align="center"><strong>One Thousand  Pounds Cash</strong></h1>
<p><strong>Bands will be judged by three  judges who will make up 75% of the marking, the remaining 25% of the marks will  made up by way of a clapometer which will record the people`s choice so you  need to bring all your avid fans to give yourselves a fighting chance.</strong><br>
    <strong>Judges will award marks for a  band`s stage presentation, individual and collective musicianship.</strong></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Some details are approx as we do not know exactly how many bands will  apply these will become more definite just before the competition commences, at  which point we will publish exact numbers.<br>
  The entry fee per band is &pound;10 payable on the night of the band`s first  performance.<br>
  So good luck and get rehearsing.</p>
